JOHANNESBURG - The trial against a man accused of trying to assassinate state officials is expected to start in the Johannesburg magistrate s court on Thursday. Elvis Ramosebudi initially faced charges for attempting a coup, but the National Prosecuting Authority found no evidence to support the charge.Ramosebudi is accused of planning to murder the President and a number of officials perceived as beneficiaries of state capture.READ: Alleged assasination plotter granted bailHe was arrested by the Hawks in April, after an undercover investigation.In May he was granted R3,000 bail with conditions.The 33-year old is facing incitement to commit murder charges.eNCA